<ul>
<li class="aflsp_faq_accordian-slide">
<div class="head clearfix qna">
<div class="question_no left">6.</div>
<div class="question remain">How do I obtain a Participating University recommendation?</div>
<div class="button"></div>
</div>
<div class="detail qna">
<div class="detail_content" style="text-align: justify;">After online application closes on 28 February 2015, Bai Xian Asia Institute will forward a complete list of registered candidates to Participating Universities (&ldquo;PU&rdquo;). &nbsp;Subject to each PU&rsquo;s own admission timetable, the PU will recommend up to 10 candidates from the Institute's list of registered candidates for interview by the BXAI Selection Panel. The usual vetting and verification of the candidate&rsquo;s application will be done by the PU&rsquo;s admission officer.</div>
</div>
</li>
<li class="aflsp_faq_accordian-slide">
<div class="head clearfix qna">
<div class="question_no left">7.</div>
<div class="question remain">What should I expect of the interview?</div>
<div class="button"></div>
</div>
<div class="detail qna">
<div class="detail_content" style="text-align: justify;">The <span>BXAI Selection Panel will take into consideration </span>a candidate's depth of engagement, accomplishments, and aspirations. &nbsp;Candidates are expected to demonstrate intellectual and academic potential of a high standard, exceptional character, knowledge of global issues, and a commitment to public service. &nbsp;Interview topics will therefore be wide-ranging in nature, designed to assess candidates in light of the Institute&rsquo;s mission and vision.</div>
</div>
</li>
<li class="aflsp_faq_accordian-slide">
<div class="head clearfix qna">
<div class="question_no left">8.</div>
<div class="question remain">What if I cannot commit to attending the BXAI Summer Program?</div>
<div class="button"></div>
</div>
<div class="detail qna">
<div class="detail_content" style="text-align: justify;">The BXAI Summer Program is a crucial aspect of the Asian Future Leaders Scholarship Program ("AFLSP") as it brings all Bai Xian Asian Scholars together to reside in one location over 4 weeks in summer, where they have a common platform to share their AFLSP experiences. &nbsp;All Bai Xian Asian Scholars must commit to attending the BXAI Summer Program, and are required to sign a Commitment Letter at the time of accepting the AFLSP Scholarship.</div>
</div>
</li>
<li class="aflsp_faq_accordian-slide">
<div class="head clearfix qna">
<div class="question_no left">9.</div>
<div class="question remain">If I am not selected for the AFLSP Scholarship this year, may I re-apply next year?</div>
<div class="button"></div>
</div>
<div class="detail qna">
<div class="detail_content">Yes.</div>
</div>
</li>
<li class="aflsp_faq_accordian-slide">
<div class="head clearfix qna">
<div class="question_no left">10.</div>
<div class="question remain">What is a PU application number?</div>
<div class="button"></div>
</div>
<div class="detail qna">
<div class="detail_content" style="text-align: justify;">A PU application number is the reference number you receive from a Participating University when submitting an application. You can use this number to register on our website.</div>
</div>
</li>
<li class="aflsp_faq_accordian-slide">
<div class="head clearfix qna">
<div class="question_no left">11.</div>
<div class="question remain">Do I qualify for applying for a scholarship?</div>
<div class="button"></div>
</div>
<div class="detail qna">
<div class="detail_content" style="text-align: justify;">It depends on which of our partner universities you are interested in applying to.<br /><br />All Asian students are eligible to apply for the Asian Future Leaders Scholarship Program ("AFLSP") at one of our Anchor Universities, which currently include (1) Hitotsubashi University, (2) Hong Kong University of Science and Technology, (3) Kyoto University, (4) Peking University, (5) Waseda University, and (6) Zhejiang University. The Institute encourages students who are interested in applying for the AFLSP at one of our Anchor Universities to contact the relevant university office/program administrator to express their interest.<br /><br />If you are of Chinese, Japanese or Korea ethnic origin, or if your country of residence/ citizenship is in Mainland China, Hong Kong SAR, Macao SAR, Taiwan, Japan, or Korea, you are eligible to apply for the Asian Future Leaders Scholarship Program Pool of scholarships for Participating Universities on our website, which currently include (1) Fudan University, (2) Keio University, (3) Kyushu University, (4) National Taiwan University, (5) Seoul National University, (6) Shanghai Jiao Tong University, (7) The Chinese University of Hong Kong, (8) The University of Hong Kong, (9) The University of Tokyo, and (10) Tsinghua University.<br /><br />Please be reminded that the AFLSP supports Asian students over the full course of their degree program. Students currently enrolled at one of our partner universities are not eligible for the scholarship supporting their current degree program. However, please consider us if you are interested in pursuing further studies at one of our Anchor or Participating Universities after completion of your current degree program.<br /><br />Please also be reminded that the AFLSP only supports Asian students pursuing overseas studies at an Anchor or Participating University in a region other than their country of residence/citizenship/ethnic origin.</div>
</div>
</li>
<li class="aflsp_faq_accordian-slide">
<div class="head clearfix qna">
<div class="question_no left">12.</div>
<div class="question remain">I am currently enrolled at one of the Participating Universities, can I apply for the AFLSP supporting my current degree studies?</div>
<div class="button"></div>
</div>
<div class="detail qna">
<div class="detail_content" style="text-align: justify;">The AFLSP supports Asian students over the full course of their degree program. Students currently enrolled at one of our partner universities are not eligible for the scholarship supporting their current degree program. However, please consider us if you are interested in pursuing further studies at one of our Anchor or Participating Universities after completion of your current degree program.<br /><br />All Asian students are eligible to apply for the Asian Future Leaders Scholarship Program ("AFLSP") at one of our Anchor Universities, which currently include (1) Hitotsubashi University, (2) Hong Kong University of Science and Technology, (3) Kyoto University, (4) Peking University, (5) Waseda University, and (6) Zhejiang University. The Institute encourages students who are interested in applying for the AFLSP at one of our Anchor Universities to contact the relevant university office/program administrator to express their interest.<br /><br />If you are of Chinese, Japanese or Korea ethnic origin, or if your country of residence/ citizenship is in Mainland China, Hong Kong SAR, Macao SAR, Taiwan, Japan, or Korea, you are eligible to apply for the Asian Future Leaders Scholarship Program Pool of scholarships for Participating Universities on our website, which currently include (1) Fudan University, (2) Keio University, (3) Kyushu University, (4) National Taiwan University, (5) Seoul National University, (6) Shanghai Jiao Tong University, (7) The Chinese University of Hong Kong, (8) The University of Hong Kong, (9) The University of Tokyo, and (10) Tsinghua University.<br /><br />Please be reminded that the AFLSP only supports Asian students pursuing overseas studies at an Anchor or Participating University in a region other than their country of residence/citizenship/ethnic origin.</div>
</div>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
